title: 811527 ACT2022FD_FC-Ma_48
frontText: What is the formula for finding the number of possible permutations (orderings) of a set?
backText:
n!
where n stands for the number of elements in the set
Factorial (!) is determined by multiplying n by all of the positive integers below n. For example, 5! = 5 x 4 x 3 x 2 x 1.
